Source: libfreedomesound
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: FreeDome Project <freedome@nativemind.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 12), cmake (>= 3.16), libavformat-dev, libavcodec-dev, libavutil-dev, libswscale-dev, libswresample-dev, pkg-config, libcuda-dev [amd64], nvidia-cuda-toolkit [amd64], ocl-icd-opencl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.5.0
Homepage: https://github.com/freedome/freedomesound

Package: libfreedomesound2
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: FreeDome Sound processing library - runtime
 FreeDome Sound is a quantum-enhanced audio processing library designed 
 for immersive dome projection systems. It provides advanced spatial audio 
 processing, quantum feedback systems, and consciousness integration 
 capabilities for professional audio applications.
 .
 This package contains the shared libraries.

Package: libfreedomesound-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: libfreedomesound2 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}, libavformat-dev, libavcodec-dev, libavutil-dev, libswscale-dev, libswresample-dev, libcuda-dev [amd64], ocl-icd-opencl-dev
Description: FreeDome Sound processing library - development files
 FreeDome Sound is a quantum-enhanced audio processing library designed 
 for immersive dome projection systems. It provides advanced spatial audio 
 processing, quantum feedback systems, and consciousness integration 
 capabilities for professional audio applications.
 .
 This package contains the header files and static libraries needed for
 developing applications that use FreeDome Sound.

Package: freedomesound-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: libfreedomesound2 (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: FreeDome Sound processing tools
 FreeDome Sound is a quantum-enhanced audio processing library designed 
 for immersive dome projection systems.
 .
 This package contains command-line tools and utilities for working with
 FreeDome Sound audio processing.
